<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Wright</emphasis>
3094
<potBibRef>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Shafer</emphasis>
2607
</potBibRef>
from Camaguey and sine data from Bahamas (K) have 3-5 lobed leaves. Other specimens have entire leaves.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="beyeriana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea beyeriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known from the type. We believe it is an entire-leaved form of 
<taxonomicName authority="Griseb." authorityName="Griseb." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="microdactyla">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. microdactyla</emphasis>
Griseb.
</taxonomicName>
, based on the leaf shape and the reddish sepals. Urban (1925: 425) suggested an affinity with 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fuchsioides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea fuchsioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and it is not unlike the type of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="fuchsioides" variety="glabra">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. fuchsioides</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">glabra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is an even better match for 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Wright</emphasis>
3102, the type of 
<taxonomicName authority="House." authorityName="House." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Exogonium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="microdactylum" variety="integrifolium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Exogonium microdactylum</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">integrifolium</emphasis>
House.
</taxonomicName>
(Wood and Scotland 2017c).
</paragraph>
